{"name":"Hugin and Munin","type":"gift","img":"icons/creatures/birds/corvid-raven-purple.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, you can ask for advice from Hugin and Munin, the ravens of Father Odin. Ask the Storyteller a question, choosing from among: **'Where should I go?'** **'How can I defeat that enemy?'** **'What is missing in my search?'** The Storyteller will answer with a cryptic sentence, which always includes a useful hint. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks against an attack from a non-human creature, thanks to the blessing of Odin himself. **Cost:** At the beginning of each Scene, you must spend 1 Soma to feed the spirits of Hugin and Munin, or lose the use of this Gift for the rest of the Scenario.</p>","notes":"Hugin (Thought) and Munin (Memory) are Odin's ravens from Norse mythology. In Tuvstarr's Reflection, even the ancient gods want to stop the corruption spreading across the land. Random encounter 2 in the Wild Forest. The ravens approach and mentally communicate, offering their blessing. The cryptic answers guide without giving away solutions. The +1 success vs non-human creatures helps against Fairies, Hulder, Skutt, trolls, etc. Must pay 1 Soma at scene start to keep the gift active (feeding their spirits). Special rule: Unlike normal Scenario Gifts, this can be acquired WITHOUT an Interlude—immediately upon making the pact.","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","requirement":"Meet Hugin and Munin in the Wild Forest and make a pact with them. (NO INTERLUDE REQUIRED in Sherazade stories)","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","sourceDirectory":"tuvstarrs-reflection","legacyId":"3d35aa895a3ee9ed","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Tuvstarrs Reflection"}},"_id":"Y0P3X9PBtRyhMw9V"}
{"name":"Lance of the Fallen Knight","type":"gift","img":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-flared-purple.webp","system":{"description":"<p>When you wield this spear and obtain an Outcome with Increment on an attack, you can inflict 1 Additional Wound. The tip of the lance can ignite at will, casting light and allowing you to have a burning fire always near at hand. This enchanted ashwood spear with an iron point belonged to one of the brave knights who died searching for Princess Tuvstarr.</p>","notes":"Random encounter 3 in the Wild Forest. Black fumes fill the air, bubbles emerge from a dark pond. A knight in rusty armor lies dead, eyes white and puffy. The corpse holds this ashwood spear with iron point. Mechanical benefits: 1) +1 Wound on Increment attacks (powerful offensive boost). 2) Ignites at will for light and fire source (utility in dark forest). If the Hunters meet the Gallant Knight in the Dream World and possess this lance, he will ask them to return it to the castle in the real world as proof of his fallen brothers' sacrifice. The lance is a symbol of duty and sacrifice. Special rule: Can be acquired WITHOUT an Interlude—immediately upon taking it from the corpse.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","requirement":"Collect the lance from the dead knight's body found near a dark pond in the Wild Forest. (NO INTERLUDE REQUIRED in Sherazade stories)","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","successes":0},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","category":"scenario","scenario":"Tuvstarrs Reflection","scenarioSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","sourceDirectory":"tuvstarrs-reflection","legacyId":"8092a773dfdcbbf6","legacyType":"item","folderName":"Tuvstarrs Reflection"}},"_id":"U158ohNYaxd6xFL6"}
